Hello Why is the sun yellow?

The sun is a star that emits light and heat due to nuclear fusion. The process by which the sun generates energy is called nuclear fusion. In nuclear fusion, two atoms or molecules combine to form a larger atom, releasing a lot of energy in the process. The energy released by nuclear fusion is what gives the sun its yellow color.
